      • proximity

        public abstract PlaceOptions.Builder proximity(@Nullable
                                               com.mapbox.geojson.Point proximity)
        Bias local results based on a provided Point. This oftentimes increases accuracy in the returned results.
        Parameters:
        proximity - a point defining the proximity you'd like to bias the results around
        Returns:
        this builder instance for chaining options together
        Since:
        0.1.0

      • language

        public abstract PlaceOptions.Builder language(@Nullable
                                              String language)
        Specify the language to use for response text and, for forward geocoding, query result weighting. Options are IETF language tags comprised of a mandatory ISO 639-1 language code and optionally one or more IETF subtags for country or script. More than one value can also be specified, separated by commas.
        Parameters:
        language - a string representing the language as a locale
        Returns:
        this builder instance for chaining options together
        Since:
        0.1.0

      • geocodingTypes

        public PlaceOptions.Builder geocodingTypes(@NonNull
                                           String... geocodingTypes)
        This optionally can be set to filter the results returned inside the suggestions.

        Note that GeocodingCriteria.TYPE_POI_LANDMARK returns a subset of the results returned by GeocodingCriteria.TYPE_POI. More than one type can be specified.

        Parameters:
        geocodingTypes - the applied filter(s) specifically from GeocodingCriteria.GeocodingTypeCriteria
        Returns:
        this builder instance for chaining options together
        Since:
        0.1.0

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        this builder instance for chaining options together
        Since:

                                 double minY,

                                 double maxY)
        Limit results to a bounding box.
        Parameters:
        minX - a longitude coordinate which defines the right of the bounding box when the map's cardinal direction is north
        minY - a latitude coordinate which defines the bottom of the bounding box when the map's cardinal direction is north
        maxX - a longitude coordinate which defines the left of the bounding box when the map's cardinal direction is north
        maxY - a latitude coordinate which defines the top of the bounding box when the map's cardinal direction is north
        Returns:
        this builder instance for chaining options together
        Since:
        0.1.0

      • addInjectedFeature

        public PlaceOptions.Builder addInjectedFeature(com.mapbox.api.geocoding.v5.models.CarmenFeature carmenFeature)
        Optionally inject CarmenFeatures into the suggestion view so users can access points of interest quickly without typing a single character. Typical places include, the users home, work, or favorite POI.
        Parameters:
        carmenFeature - a list of serialized CarmenFeatures which show immediately when the autocomplete UI is displayed to the user
        Returns:
        this builder instance for chaining options together
        Since:
        0.1.0
